# Internal working docs + tooling config: committed to the (private) GitHub repo as a living
# backup, but excluded from every Vercel deployment — they are never uploaded, never part of
# the deployment's source snapshot, and never served. The build needs none of them.
# Note: serving was never the risk (only build output + /public are ever served); this file
# exists so these files don't LIVE on Vercel at all.
# 2026-07-24: root cleanup landed — everything internal (handoff docs, copy drafts, scratch,
# scripts) now lives under /_internal/, so one line covers it all.
/_internal/
/.agents
/.claude
/.vscode
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
MANAGER.md
COMPONENTS.md
SANITY-SETUP.md
README.md
skills-lock.json
